{"id":"math210-deriv_poly210-ap001","cid":"MATH 210","topic":"Applications of Derivatives","subtopic":"Evaluating f'(x) at a point","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Let f(x) = {pa}x^3 + {pb}x^2 + {pc}x + {pd}. Compute f'({x_val}) to determine whether f is increasing or decreasing at that point.","params":{"pa":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":2},"pb":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":0},"pc":{"type":"int","min":-4,"max":4},"pd":{"type":"int","min":-4,"max":4},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":-2,"max":2}},"answer_expr":"deriv_poly210","steps":["f'(x) = {da}x^2 + {db}x + {dc}.","f'({x_val}) = {answer_deriv_poly210}.","If f'({x_val}) > 0 the function is increasing; if < 0 it is decreasing."],"tags":["calculus","applications","increasing-decreasing","critical-points"]}
